The workers have been protesting since last October after a collective
agreement on the salary hikes of estate workers[ was not
signed.](http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2018/10/28/news-features/salary-dispute-
estate-workers) The workers
[rejected](http://www.sundaytimes.lk/190113/business-times/storm-in-a-teacup-
reaches-boiling-point-329861.html) a 20 percent (Rs.100) increase proposed by
the Employers’ Federation of Ceylon (EFC), an organization that represents
plantation companies.

